{
  "texts": [
    "Feedback which were not mentioned in the change summary were excluded.",
    "Finally, we include all permutations of linearized feedback from the set of feedback, in order to teach the model the order-independence of the feedback when performing the edit.",
    "Edit Preference is used to train a model to distinguish good edits from unsatisfactory edits.",
    "The first type of unsatisfactory edits are bad edits that are not based on the feedback, but instead on what an edit annotator thought was needed (see Appendix C for details).",
    "This was a common issue during our initial annotation."
  ]
}